description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title - Paediatric Specialist Speech And Language Therapist – Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location – Cheltenham/countywide service &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - £31,365 to £37,890 per annum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: 37.5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking a skilled clinician to join our dynamic and friendly team providing Speech &amp; Language Therapy services to children &amp; young people in Gloucestershire.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post offers an opportunity to work with early years and mainstream children in clinic, home and education settings. We a work creatively with parents and settings to provide appropriate intervention packages using a care aims framework.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The use of Attend Anywhere for video appointments has been a recent addition to the team’s skill set.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We currently offer access to the service within 8 weeks.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a county wide service a flexible approach to working will be expected to meet demand.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Speech and Language Therapy Service covers the whole county of Gloucestershire and offers regular support through whole team meetings, client group meetings, clinical supervision, as well as from Highly Specialist therapists in Language Disorder, Hearing Impairment, ASD, Cleft Palate, Fluency and Learning Difficulties.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locality Leads: Sue Douglass or Louise Wheatley on 0300 421 8937&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: susan.douglass@ghc.nhs.uk louise.wheatley@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shortlisting date: 11th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
